Sentencas: In this study, we have successfully fabricated yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte thin films by aerosol-assisted chemical vapor deposition (AACVD) for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) working at an intermediate temperature range under 600.
Titulo: High Performance Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Thin Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Membrane Prepared by Aerosol-Assisted Chemical Vapor Deposition
High Performance Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Thin Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Membrane Prepared by Aerosol-Assisted Chemical Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: The mix ratio of precursor sources and the deposition temperature of the AACVD process are optimized to obtain target composition and crystal structure of the YSZ film.
Titulo: High Performance Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Thin Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Membrane Prepared by Aerosol-Assisted Chemical Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: The optimized AACVD YSZ membrane is incorporated onto Ni-YSZ anodes supported without interlayers for evaluation of SOFC performance.
Titulo: High Performance Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Thin Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Membrane Prepared by Aerosol-Assisted Chemical Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: Fully dense 1-mu m-thick AACVD YSZ electrolyte successfully produces a stable open circuit voltage (OCV) greater than 1 V at all test temperatures in the range of 450- 600.
Titulo: High Performance Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Thin Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Membrane Prepared by Aerosol-Assisted Chemical Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: degrees C. Power output of the test cell is measured as about 600 mW cm(-2) at 600.
Titulo: High Performance Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Thin Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Membrane Prepared by Aerosol-Assisted Chemical Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: degrees C. Performance of our cell is compared to that of a reference cell with the same structure but with an 8-mu m-thick membrane produced by screen-printing; our cell produces 1.4 to 4 times as much power as the reference cell at all test temperatures.
Titulo: High Performance Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Thin Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Membrane Prepared by Aerosol-Assisted Chemical Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance analysis has confirmed that the power enhancement with the thin AACVD YSZ membrane is due to effective reduction of both ohmic and polarization resistances.
Titulo: High Performance Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells with Thin Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Membrane Prepared by Aerosol-Assisted Chemical Vapor Deposition
